					<div class="module">
						<h2>Project Scope</h2>
						<ul>
						
							<li>Posters</li>
						
							<li>Art Direction</li>
						
							<li>Illustration</li>
						
						</ul>	

						<p>Wilco is a great American rock band. They’ve been tinkering with, and reinventing, their brand of pop Americana since 1994.
</p>
					</div>
					<p class="btn-alt"><a href="/site/detail/wilco-collection">See The Full Project</a></p>						
				</div>

				<div class="col module">

					<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>Since 2004, we&#8217;ve been creating posters for the iconic American band Wilco.</p>

<h2>Problem</h2>
<p>As the band has shapeshifted over the years through various lineups and styles, they&#8217;ve sought to maintain a consistent visual authenticity with all of their products. Conversely, the gig poster scene has grown oversaturated with ephemeral solutions and hackneyed visual motifs.</p>


					
					<blockquote>
						
						<p>&ldquo;Working with The Heads of State has produced some of the best work we've ever commissioned. The Radio City poster? Coney Island? 9.30 club? Classics.&rdquo;</p>
						<p class="who">- Ben Levin | Tony Margherita Management
</p>
						
					</blockquote>

					<h2>Solution</h2>
Combining the elegance of theatre posters and vintage movie one-sheets with inside jokes, lyrical references, and other winks and nods that speak directly to us first and foremost as fans of the music, we’ve created some of our best known work for a client that respects graphic design and illustration.

				</div>
				
